object.script:
-- -> 0deg V90deg <180deg ^270deg tyaw = 0 yawup = 1 targets = {} srans = {45,60,90,180} mode = 1 sran = srans[mode] touched = false
zoom = {5000,2500,1000,500,50} zoomMode = 1 clicked = false
found = {}
function onTick() inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isPressed = input.getBool(1) tdis = input.getNumber(7) --sran = input.getNumber(8) --45d, 90d, 180d sspd = input.getNumber(8) --scanspeed tdet = input.getBool(3) --target detected revs = input.getBool(4) --downward?
if (math.abs(tyaw)>sran) and (sran~=180) then yawup = yawup*-1 end tyaw = tyaw + yawup*sspd/5 if tyaw>=180 then tyaw = -180 end
for i,v in ipairs(found) do v[3] = v[3]-1 if v[3]<0 then table.remove(found,i) end end
if tdet then table.insert(found, {tyaw, tdis, 255}) end
isPressingRectangle = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 2,2,8,8)
if isPressingRectangle then clicked = true end
if not isPressed then if clicked then zoomMode = (zoomMode+1)%#zoom clicked = false elseif touched then mode = (mode+1)%#srans yawup = 1 tyaw = 0 found = nil found = {} end end touched = isPressed sran = srans[mode+1]
if revs then output.setNumber(1, -tyaw/360) else output.setNumber(1, tyaw/360) end output.setNumber(2, radius) output.setNumber(3, centerH) end
function drawPixel(x, y) screen.drawText(x-1, y-4, ".") end
function drawArcDash(x, y, r, st, w) for i=st, (st+w)-1 do x1, y1 = x + r*math.cos(math.rad(i)), y + r*math.sin(math.rad(i)) drawPixel(x1,y1) end end
function drawBackground(x, y, r, st, w) local k = math.floor(math.log(r)) for i=1, k do drawArcDash(x, y, r*i/k, st, w) end if sran ~= 180 then x1, y1 = x + r*math.cos(math.rad(st)), y + r*math.sin(math.rad(st)) screen.drawLine(x, y, x1, y1) x1, y1 = x + r*math.cos(math.rad(st+w)), y + r*math.sin(math.rad(st+w)) screen.drawLine(x, y, x1, y1) end end
function drawButton(x,y,w,h) if clicked then screen.setColor(255,255,0) else screen.setColor(0,64,0) end screen.drawRect(x, y, w, h) screen.drawTextBox(x+1, y+1, w, h, "R", 0, 0) end
function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() screenH, screenW = screen.getHeight(), screen.getWidth() screen.setColor(0,32,0)
if sran ~= 180 then radius = screenW/(2*math.sin(math.rad(sran)))*0.9 else radius = screenH/2*0.9 end centerH = screenH/2 + screenH*(180-sran)/300
drawBackground(screenW/2, centerH, radius, 270-sran, 2*sran)
x3, y3 = screenW/2 + radius*math.cos(math.rad(tyaw-90)), centerH + radius*math.sin(math.rad(tyaw-90)) screen.drawLine(screenW/2, centerH, x3, y3)
--screen.drawText(0,0,screenW.."x"..screenH) --screen.drawText(0, 0, sran*2) screen.drawTextBox(0, 0, screenW, screenH, zoom[zoomMode+1].."m", 1, -1)
for i, v in ipairs(found) do screen.setColor(0, 255, 0, v[3]) xt, yt = screenW/2 + radius*v[2]/zoom[zoomMode+1]*math.cos(math.rad(v[1]-90)), centerH + radius*v[2]/zoom[zoomMode+1]*math.sin(math.rad(v[1]-90)) drawPixel(xt, yt) end
--screen.drawText(screenW/2, centerH, tyaw)
drawButton(2,2,8,8)
end

object.script:
tilt = 0 rollAngle = 0 vertCheck = true lineDist = property.getNumber('Degrees per Line') pixPerDegree = property.getNumber('Pixels per Degree') maxLineWidth = property.getNumber('Maximum Line Length as Screen Percent') lineDivideFactor = (property.getNumber('Minimum Line Length as Percent of Max')+1)*90 if property.getBool('Vertical Flip') then yMod = -1 else yMod = 1 end
function onTick() tilt = input.getNumber(1)*360 -- Tilt (Forward tilt sensor) supplied through composite 1 maxAngle = 90-math.abs(tilt) rollAngle = (input.getNumber(2)*360)/maxAngle*90 -- Roll (Right tilt sensor) supplied through composite 2 vertCheck = input.getNumber(3)>=0 if not vertCheck then -- Vertical check (Up tilt sensor) supplied through composite 3 tilt = tilt*-1 rollAngle = rollAngle*-1 end end
function calcXY(x,y,bearing,distance) bearing = math.rad(bearing + 90) y = y+math.cos(bearing) * -distance x = x+math.sin(bearing) * distance return x,y end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
if vertCheck then screen.setColor(0,50,0) else screen.setColor(0,50,0) end for lineAngle = -90, 90, lineDist do if lineAngle>0 and vertCheck then screen.setColor(0,50,0) elseif lineAngle>0 and not vertCheck then screen.setColor(0,50,0) end lineLen = (maxLineWidth*w)*(1-math.abs(lineAngle)/lineDivideFactor) currentY = (tilt-lineAngle)*pixPerDegree*yMod mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,currentY) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,lineLen/2) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,lineLen/2) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) end centerY = h/2+tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod screen.setColor(0,50,0) mX, mY = calcXY(w/2,h/2,rollAngle+90,tilt*pixPerDegree*yMod) lX, lY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle,100) rX, rY = calcXY(mX,mY,rollAngle+180,100) screen.drawLine(lX,lY,rX,rY) screen.setColor(0,115,0) screen.drawRectF(w/2-1,h/2,2,2) end

object.script:
function onTick() -- Read the touchscreen data from the script's composite input inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4) isPressed = input.getBool(1) output.setBool(10, U) output.setBool(11, D) output.setBool(12, L) output.setBool(13, R) output.setBool(14, Plus) output.setBool(15, Minus) output.setBool(16, Infra)
-- Check if the player is pressing the rectangle at (10, 10) with width and height of 20px isPressingRectangleU = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, w/2-3, 0, 6, 4) isPressingRectangleD = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, w/2-3, h-5, 6, 4) isPressingRectangleL = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 0, h/2-4, 4, 6) isPressingRectangleR = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, w-5, h/2-4, 4, 6) isPressingRectanglePlus = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 2, h-4, 3, 3) isPressingRectangleMinus = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, 6, h-4, 3, 3) isPressingRectangleInfra = isPressed and isPointInRectangle(inputX, inputY, w-9, h-6, 8, 6)
-- Set the composite output, on/off channel 1 output.setBool(1, isPressingRectangle) end
-- Returns true if the point (x, y) is inside the rectangle at (rectX, rectY) with width rectW and height rectH function isPointInRectangle(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0, 255, 0, 140)
-- Draw a rectangle that fills in when the player is pressing it if isPressingRectangleU then screen.drawRectF(w/2-3, 0, 6, 4) U = true else screen.drawRect(w/2-3, 0, 6, 4) U = false end if isPressingRectangleD then screen.drawRectF(w/2-3, h-5, 6, 4) D = true else screen.drawRect(w/2-3, h-5, 6, 4) D = false end if isPressingRectangleL then screen.drawRectF(0, h/2-4, 4, 6) L = true else screen.drawRect(0, h/2-4, 4, 6) L = false end if isPressingRectangleR then screen.drawRectF(w-5, h/2-4, 4, 6) R = true else screen.drawRect(w-5, h/2-4, 4, 6) R = false end if isPressingRectanglePlus then screen.drawRectF(2, h-4, 3, 3) Plus = true else screen.drawLine(2, h-3, 5, h-3) screen.drawLine(3, h-2, 3, h-5) Plus = false end if isPressingRectangleMinus then screen.drawRectF(6, h-4, 3, 3) Minus = true else screen.drawLine(6, h-3, 9, h-3) Minus = false end if isPressingRectangleInfra then screen.drawRectF(w-9, h-6, 8, 6) Infra = true else screen.drawText(w-9, h-6, "IR") Infra = false end
end
